    • Field Detail

      • constraintrange

        @Option
public double[] constraintrange
        The domain range to which the filter on the dimension is constrained. Must be an array of "[fromValue, toValue]" with finite numbers as elements.

      • label

        @Option
public String label
        The shown name of the dimension.

      • range

        @Option
public double[] range
        The domain range that represents the full, shown axis extent. Defaults to the "values" extent. Must be an array of "[fromValue, toValue]" with finite numbers as elements.

      • tickformat

        @Option
public String tickformat
        The tick label formatting rule using d3 formatting mini-language which is similar to those of Python. See d3 format reference.

      • ticktext

        @Option
public String[] ticktext
        The text displayed at the ticks position via "tickvals". Only has an effect if "tickmode" is set to "array". Used with "tickvals".

      • tickvals

        @Option
public double[] tickvals
        The values at which ticks on this axis appear. Only has an effect if "tickmode" is set to "array". Used with "ticktext".

      • values

        @Option
public double[] values
        Dimension values. "values[n]" represents the value of the "n"th point in the dataset, therefore the "values" vector for all dimensions must be the same (longer vectors will be truncated). Each value must be a finite number.

      • visible

        @Option
public Boolean visible
        Shows the dimension when set to true. Hides the dimension for false.

        Default: true
